    <thetext>The second NOTE in 12.1.1.2 refers to the steps 4 and 5, but it should refer to steps 5-6 instead. 

Also the second example in the second NOTE is no longer valid, because the spec has been (partially?) updated to use the completion reform semantics, so `eval(&quot;1; {}&quot;)` no longer evaluates to `1` but instead to `undefined`.


And step 4 could actually be removed, because s.[[value]] is never empty when s.[[type]] == throw.</thetext>
